Date: Thu, 29 Jan 2026 13:38:46 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 10/22] fix(provisioning): Handle role removal when IdP claims
 are empty

Previously, when a user was removed from roles in the IdP:
- Instance role: No change was made (user kept their existing role)
- Project roles: No change was made (user kept access to all projects)

Now, when provisioning is enabled:
- Empty/missing instance role claim: User is downgraded to global:member
- Empty/missing project roles claim: User loses access to all projects
- Partial project role changes: Access is removed from projects no longer in claims

This ensures that role changes in the IdP are properly reflected in n8n,
including role revocation/removal scenarios.
